### Author Creation

This endpoint allows the creation of a new author.

#### Request Body

- `name` (string, required): The name of the author.

- `bio` (string, required): A brief biography of the author.


#### Response

The response is in JSON format with the following schema:

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "name": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "bio": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "_id": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "createdAt": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "updatedAt": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "__v": {
            "type": "number"
        }
    }
}

 ```

#### Example

Request:

``` json
{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "bio": "An accomplished author"
}

 ```

Response:

``` json
{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "bio": "An accomplished author",
    "_id": "some_id",
    "createdAt": "2022-01-01T00:00:00.000Z",
    "updatedAt": "2022-01-01T00:00:00.000Z",
    "__v": 0
}

 ```

The endpoint retrieves a list of authors.

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "author": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "_id": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "name": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "bio": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "createdAt": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "updatedAt": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "__v": {
            "type": "integer"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

### GET /api/v1/author/:id

This endpoint retrieves author details based on the provided ID.

#### Request

No request body is required for this endpoint.

- `:id` (path parameter) - The unique identifier of the author.


#### Response

The response will be in JSON format and will contain the author details. The response schema is as follows:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "author": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "_id": { "type": "string" },
        "name": { "type": "string" },
        "bio": { "type": "string" },
        "createdAt": { "type": "string" },
        "updatedAt": { "type": "string" },
        "__v": { "type": "number" },
        "photo": { "type": "string" }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

In case the author with the provided ID is not found, the response will have a status code of 404 and an empty JSON object with a "message" property.

