### Update Category

This endpoint is used to update a specific category.

#### Request

- Method: PUT

- URL: `http://localhost:3000/api/v1/category/:id`

- { "description": "lucu ajah"


#### Response

The response for this request can be represented as a JSON schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "category": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "_id": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "name": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "description": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "createdAt": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "updatedAt": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "__v": {
          "type": "number"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

The API endpoint sends an HTTP DELETE request to delete a category based on the provided ID. Upon successful execution, the response will have a status code of 200 and a JSON content type. The response body will consist of a JSON object with a "message" key, which may be empty. Below is the JSON schema for the response:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```

